<TITLE> Murder case filed by Nurul Islam's family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  A murder case has been filed by Nurul Islam's family, police said on Sunday, in the wake of the fire five days ago that claimed the lives of both the Ganotontree Party president and his son. "Islam's brother-in-law ABM Hasan filed the case, naming no accused, with Mohammadpur police," sub-inspector Borhan Uddin Ahmed said. The case alleges that the deaths were caused by fire started purposely with combustible items, the police officer said. "Investigations have already started." Immediately after the fire, the fire service investigation report attributed it to a short circuit. Fire service director general brigadier general Abu Nayeem Mohammad Shahidullah told bdnews24.com their probe did not find signs of combustibles, explosives or any other suspicious materials. He said positive proof was found of a short circuit as the cause of the fire, and sent to the home ministry. The case registered with the police has claimed that Islam had received threats by phone for some time. The Ganotontree Party president was the Awami League-led alliances nominee for the Noakhali-1 seat. Tamohar Islam died in the blaze in the early hours of Dec 3. His father, who suffered critical burns, succumbed to his injuries at Dhaka Combined Military Hospital on the evening of Dec 4. No other members of the family were at home when the fire broke out; Islam's wife and daughter who were in the United States returned home on Thursday night. bdnew
